result.execSummary:
Joseph O Rabaca was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Joseph O Rabaca was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Joseph O Rabaca

records.addlTxt: Received and Filed: Attorney Haley Wentz

Defendant Joseph O Rabaca not in court.  Nate K. McClure appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant has been turned over to the State of Illinois, DuPage County on 06/27/22. On motion of the state, Court ordered case closed.

Defendant Joseph O Rabaca in court with attorney Haley E Wentz.  Defendant Joseph O Rabaca in custody.  Jessica Ann Behling appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Joseph O Rabaca appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Childs, Branch 02.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of rights and right to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  Court found the defendant is the person wanted in the State of Illinois.  Defendant waived extradition.  Signed Waiver of Extradition received and filed.  Court ordered the defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.   This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Status conference scheduled for July 5, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
